Package se.aqba.framework.elpollo

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ElPollo.Packages.Listener
    A package load listener.
    ElPollo.Resources.Listener
    A package resource load listener.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ElPollo
    Class that contains various classes and methods to add method overrides and replace resources.


    To find out how to load your override classes, look at ElPolloModuleLoader and ElPolloModule.
    For adding overrides, have a look at ElPollo.Packages.addListener(Listener, String...), ElPollo.MemberOverride and ElPollo.Overrides.
    Adding resource replacements can be done using ElPollo.Resources.addListener(Listener, String...) and the various addReplacement methods.
    ElPollo.MemberOverride
    Object referring to a member override.
    Cannot be instantiated directly, please use ElPollo.MemberOverride.Builder.
    ElPollo.MemberOverride.Builder
    Class that's used for building a ElPollo.MemberOverride object for use with ElPollo.Overrides.add(ElPollo.MemberOverride, String...).
    ElPollo.OverrideCall<ObjType,ReturnType>
    An alternative of ElPollo.OverrideCustom that implements a
    ElPollo.OverrideCustom<ObjType,ReturnType>
    Used as an alternative to implement a custom method in the override class.
    Instances of this object MUST implement a call method matching the original method.

    Example:
    public void call(Object obj, int arg1, String arg2)
    ElPollo.Overrides
    Used for adding new member overrides to the system.
    ElPollo.Packages
    Class used for accessing various package related classes and methods.
    ElPollo.Resources
    Class used for accessing various resource related classes and methods.
    ElPollo.Resources.DrawableForwarder
    A drawable resource forwarder.
    ElPollo.Resources.Forwarder
    A resource forwarder.
    ElPollo.Resources.ViewForwarder
    A view forwarder.
    ElPolloModule
    The base module class, override classes must implement this.
    ElPolloModuleLoader
    Class that's used for determining what classes the system should load as modules.
    A module must extend this in a class called Loader under a java sub-package called elpollo.
    For example, if your android package name is foo.bar.application, the class name must be foo.bar.application.elpollo.Loader.
